title: [Epidemiology] Public Health England COVID-19 symptomatic effectiveness study finds two doses of BNT162b2 (Pfizer) at 93.7% (95% CI, 91.6 to 95.3) vs Alpha and 88.0% (95% CI, 85.3 to 90.1) vs Delta; ChAdOx1 (Astrazeneca) at 74.5% (95% CI, 68.4 to 79.4) vs Alpha and 67.0% (95% CI, 61.3 to 71.8) vs Delta
